rComments: Great prof. Her lectures may be boring sometimes, but it's worth attending them. She cares about her students and provides help when you ask for it. She does everything in her power to make herself the best prof she can be. She provides some chances for extra grades. Overall 9/10

Nice prof, although her lectures are a bit boring and can be substituted by going to tutorials and reading the textbook. Could not simply hear her at times, but the course is not too difficult and has quite interesting albeit somewhat dense themes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Professor Cummings is the kindest teacher! She is super helpful, kind, and always always willing to go over anything if it's not clear enough. Super niceeeeee

Fairly good professor. She is clear and cares about the subject. One problem is I noticed her analyses tend to focus only on her perspective and ignore others. It is a very easy course, and despite 3 books required, I didn't even have to finish the book to get my grade ;b

Great prof! She's very nice and teaches well. Shes a bit tricky at times and her lectures are too long and can get boring. But the readings are more informative as well as tutorials. Finals exams are easy if you do readings and lecture notes thoroughly.
Awesome prof! Very helpful and caring. Loved attending her class and i thought the exams were pretty decent and fair. Highly recommend the course! :)

Awesome Professor! Actually enjoyed going to her lectures and the readings were fascinating. The exams were pretty easy. If you attend lectures and do the readings you can get a really good grade. Definitely recommend.
One of the best profs I've had at UTSC. Makes things very clear. Connects with the class really well. The class was a lot more interesting because of her teaching style.
One of the best profs I had at UTSC. Very informative, funny and approachable!
Good teacher! good lectures! and very good looking too :)
Wonderful professor!  She was very engaging and extremely approachable.  There is a lot of reading but it's very interesting!

I had prof. Cummings for one of the introductory courses as well, but just finished "Culture Through Film & Media", GREAT COURSE! Maggie is VERY helpful, answers all questions you may have, interesting lectures. She is engaging. This class focuses on how media has affected diff indigenous peoples worldwide, I found it very interesting. Easy exams.

Wonderful prof, funny and keeps you engaged...didn't mind going to her lectures at all ! Interesting class, learned alot ! Had a stupid TA though, but other than that I really enjoyed the class and prof !
Interesting class. Very clear examples. Very nice professor.

Great prof. Keeps reading material relevant and interesting. Lost my midterm (a bit irritating) but gave me alternative options to choose from. Does not move from her lecture podium but still maintains interesting lectures. This course opened my eyes to a different world and I've changed majors because of it.
very good!

Dr. Cummings is wonderful. It is easy to hang on her every word, being so engaging as she is. Very few profs can convey such a great sense of other cultures and ways of life as she can. I am an anthro major because of her.
amazing prof. easy easy exams

Prof. Cummings is the one of the rare profs who can actually keep me listening and interested throughout class. Her lectures are just awesome. If you take good notes and you pay attention to the hints she gives prior to exams, you'll do just great!

She is the most organized professor I had yet. You appreciate that when you encounter many who are not. She is very intelligent and engaging, and really gets to know her students. You really want to be in her class.

I just took this course as an elective and it turned out to be one of the best courses I've taken. Prof. Cummings is incredibly engaging and the course material is interesting too. She's very accommodating and genuinely wants her students to do well and learn. Take a class with her! (But be prepared to do a lot of reading.)

Great lecturer.  She basically points out what you need to know for the midterm from her slides alone.  I got a 90 on the midterm just from making good lecture notes, and not doing the readings.  Overall, good prof.
great professor, always fun and interesting lecutres, even when its late. very clear and easy to follow
Great teacher! She is very fun and entertaining with her lectures. Never boring. I highly recommend her class even if you have no prior interest in Anthro.
awesome teacher, enthusiastic, and easy to follow
Excellent class, excellent professor.
No Comments
Very nice and is helpful always available by email and open office hours.
